In[97]:
Model_Name = []
Rating = []
No_of_Ratings = []
Details = []
Price =[]
Location = []
for page in range(1,12):
    url = f'https://www.bikewale.com/new-bike-search/best-100cc-bikes/?sortField1=modelPopularity&sortOrder1=desc&displacementRange=1-100%2C100-110%2C110-125%2C125-150%2C150-200%2C200-250%2C250-500%2C500-10000&startType=853%2C854%2C2129&fuelType=806&pageNumber={page}'
    response = requests.get(url)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text)
    for i in soup.find_all('div',attrs={'class':'o-f7 o-o'}):
        mname = i.find('span',attrs={'class':'o-jJ o-j3 o-js o-ez'})
        rat = i.find('p',attrs={'class':'o-j1 o-cx o-jq o-d o-j o-jJ'})
        Nrat = i.find('span',attrs={'class':'o-jL o-f7 o-j0 o-jc o-fE'})
        cc = i.find('div',attrs={'class':'o-o FTJfQA o-iT o-ei'})
        price = i.find('span',attrs={'class':'o-jJ o-jr o-j3 o-kJ'})
        loc = i.find('div',attrs={'class':'o-o FTJfQA o-hj o-iT o-jK o-j1'})
    
        Model_Name.append(mname.text if mname else np.nan)
        Rating.append(rat.text if rat else np.nan )
        No_of_Ratings.append(Nrat.text if Nrat else np.nan)
        Details.append(cc.text if cc else np.nan)
        Price.append(price.text if price else np.nan)
        Location.append(loc.text if loc else np.nan)

Scraping data from web page

  • The web page has 11 pages and each page has around 30 bikes in it.
  • Each bike has model name, ratings,cc,mileage,weight,price in it.

Extracting the data:

  • The raw data has cc,power,weight,mileage in a single column to extract that we use regular expressions.
  • By using this we can have indiviual columns for each detail.
In[104]:
bike_df['Engine_CC'] = bike_df['Details'].apply(lambda x: re.findall('([0-9]+.?[0-9]+) cc',x)[0])
bike_df['Mileage'] = bike_df['Details'].astype(str).apply(
    lambda x: re.findall(r'([0-9]+\.?[0-9]*) kmpl', x)[0] if re.findall(r'([0-9]+\.?[0-9]*) kmpl', x) else np.nan)

bike_df['Power'] = bike_df['Details'].astype(str).apply(
    lambda x: re.findall(r'([0-9]+\.?[0-9]*) bhp', x)[0] if re.findall(r'([0-9]+\.?[0-9]*) bhp', x) else np.nan)

bike_df['Weight'] = bike_df['Details'].astype(str).apply(
    lambda x: re.findall(r'([0-9]+\.?[0-9]*) kg', x)[0] if re.findall(r'([0-9]+\.?[0-9]*) kg', x) else np.nan)

Extracting New Columns:

  • created some functions to extract new columns from the available data.
  • The function are applied on the dataframe using the .apply() function.
In[113]:
def Price_Category(x):
    if x>600000:
        return "Luxury"
    elif x>350000:
        return "High end"
    elif x>160000:
        return "Mid Range"
    else:
        return "Budget"
In[114]:
bike_df['Price_Category']=bike_df['Price'].apply(Price_Category)
In[115]:
def Mileage_Category(x):
    if 0<=x<=30:
        return "Low"
    elif 31<=x<=50:
        return "Medium"
    elif 51<=x<=65:
        return "Good"
    else:
        return "Excellent"
In[116]:
def Rating_Category(x):
    if 0<=x<=2.5:
        return "Poor"
    elif 2.6<=x<=3.5:
        return "Average"
    elif 3.6<=x<=4.2:
        return "Good"
    else:
        return "Excellent"
In[117]:
bike_df['Mileage_Category']=bike_df['Mileage'].apply(Mileage_Category)
bike_df['Rating_Category']=bike_df['Rating'].apply(Rating_Category)
In[118]:
bike_df['Brand'] = bike_df['Model_Name'].apply(lambda x:re.findall('[A-z]+',x)[0])
